result.execSummary:
The defendant Jermill Jordan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jermill Jordan in court with attorney Ann T. Bowe.  Peter A. Hahn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.  
*
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Sarah W.  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 months in the House of Correction with credit for 4 days time served.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 months.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-As a condition of probation, the Court ordered the defendant to serve 15 days in the House of Correction.  This time is stayed pending a review on 3/25/16.
-Successfully complete "Batterers intervention" counseling.
-Complete a parenting class.
-Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment including random urine screens.
-No controlled substances without a valid prescription.
-Successfully complete any other counseling and/or treatment deemed appropriate.
-No contact with victim, UNLESS the victim requests contact, and then only after the agent has approved a modification to no violent contact.
-Defendant may have contact with the victim through a third party to arrange time with children.
-Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges of this case, including any applicable mandatory surcharges and supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.  Court found the Domestic Abuse surcharge is applicable.  Pay Milwaukee County for attorney fees.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.
-DNA sample; pay the surcharge.
-Defendant to pay all supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.
-Obtain and maintain employment.
-No firearms; weapons.
Received and filed: Pretrial Sentence Credit, Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Memorandum of Conditions of Probation.  Court advised defendant of penalties for violating the no contact order and due to this DV conviction s/he may never possess firearms or ammunition.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for March 25, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Jermill Jordan in court with attorney Ann T. Bowe.  Jaclyn Schwartz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
Case set for jury trial.  State is ready to proceed.  Court granted defense motion to adjourn as counsel has a speedy trial in another court.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Court advised defendant that the no contact order remains in effect.  Jury trial scheduled for November 18, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Attorney Fee Trust - Escrow payment plan created 09/18/2015] to repay Milwaukee County $50.00 monthly for attorney fees. First payment commencing 09/01/15.

Defendant Jermill Jordan in court with attorney Ann T. Bowe.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Final Pretrial held.  Case remains set for jury trial in Branch 40.  As 1 of state's essential witnesses cannot appearon on 10/05/15.  Jury trial is rescheduled to 10/12/15 at 8:30 am.  Court reminds defendant the no contact order remains in effect.  Jury trial scheduled for October 12, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jermill Jordan in court with attorney Ann T. Bowe who appeared via telephone.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk:  rmm.
Pretrial Conference held.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.   Agreed Upon Request for a New Court Date is signed and filed.  Final pre-trial scheduled for September 17, 2015 at 01:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for October 5, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jermill Jordan in court.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Indigency hearing proceeded.  Court makes a finding that defendant is indigent.  Court appoints Ann Bowe as counsel for defendant at the rate of $60.00 per hour.  Attorney Bowe accepts appointment.  Order signed and filed.  Defendant shall reimburse Milwaukee County at the rate of $50.00 per month commencing 9/01/15 until paid in full. Order signed and filed.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Court advised defendant that the no contact order remains in effect.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for July 22, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Signed and Filed, No Firearms Order.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Sarah W. and Ethel L.

DEFENDANT WAS ORDERED BY THE COURT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 3:00 P.M. ON  (6/30/2015). IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.
Court ordered arrest warrant withdrawn.  Recall issued.

Defendant Jermill Jordan in court.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Dallet, Branch 40. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.   Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel.   Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance.  Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 40.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for July 13, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
